broomie
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:a person who works on the broom in a woolshed, sweeping the shearing board clean between sheep being shorn.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See: sweepo; rousie
Pronunciation:
